## Route Groups

### (auth) Route Group

Public authentication routes. Layout handles unauthenticated state.

**Location**: `apps/dashboard/src/app/[lang]/(auth)/`

**Routes**:
- `/login` - Login page

**Layout**: `apps/dashboard/src/app/(auth)/layout.tsx`

### (dashboard) Route Group

Protected dashboard routes. Layout handles authentication and redirects.

**Location**: `apps/dashboard/src/app/[lang]/(dashboard)/`

**Layout**: `apps/dashboard/src/app/[lang]/(dashboard)/layout.tsx`

**Pattern**:
```typescript
export default async function DashboardLayout({
  children,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode;
}) {
  const session = await auth.api.getSession({
    headers: await headers(),
  });

  if (!session?.user) {
    redirect("/login");
  }

  return (
    <div className="grid h-svh grid-rows-[auto_1fr]">
      <main className="overflow-auto">{children}</main>
      <BottomNavigation />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Components

### Organization

Components are organized by feature/domain under `components/app/`:

```
components/
  ├── auth/
  ├── app/
  │   ├── products/
  │   ├── orders/
  │   ├── onboarding/
  │   ├── settings/
  │   └── …
  ├── layout/
  └── shared/
```

### File Naming

- **kebab-case** for file names
- **PascalCase** for component names

### Component Pattern

```typescript
// apps/dashboard/src/components/app/orders/orders-list.tsx
"use client";

import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { appQueries } from "@/shared/api/queries";
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@dukkani/ui/components/card";

export default function OrdersList() {
  const { data: orders, isLoading } = useQuery(
    appQueries.order.all({ input: { page: 1, limit: 10 } })
  );

  if (isLoading) {
    return <div>Loading...</div>;
  }

  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>Orders</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>{/* Render orders */}</CardContent>
    </Card>
  );
}
```

### Best Practices

- Use `"use client"` directive for client components
- Use UI components from `@dukkani/ui`
- Use `appQueries` / `appMutations` for data fetching and mutations
- Handle loading and error states
- Keep components focused and reusable

## Shared Layer

The `shared/` directory is the FSD (Feature Sliced Design) shared layer. It contains all app-wide infrastructure organized into three sub-layers.

### `shared/api/` — API Infrastructure

```typescript
// Query data using appQueries
import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { appQueries } from "@/shared/api/queries";

const { data } = useQuery(appQueries.order.all({ input: { page: 1, limit: 10 } }));
const { data: product } = useQuery(appQueries.product.byId({ input: { id } }));
```

```typescript
// Mutate data using appMutations
import { useMutation } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { appMutations } from "@/shared/api/mutations";

const mutation = useMutation(appMutations.product.create());
const deleteMutation = useMutation(appMutations.order.updateStatus());
```

`appMutations` factories automatically handle cache invalidation — pass extra `onSuccess`/`onError` options to extend, not replace, the defaults.

### `shared/lib/{domain}/` — Domain Business Logic

Domain logic is grouped by feature. File suffix conventions:

| Suffix | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `controller.hook.ts` | Screen-level orchestration: composes Zustand store + appQueries + appMutations |
| `.store.ts` | Zustand store definitions (filters, pagination, selection state) |
| `.util.ts` | Pure utility functions (formatting, grouping, calculations) |
| `.hook.ts` | Domain-specific hooks that don't own full screen state |

**Controller hook pattern** — use for list pages and complex screens:

```typescript
// apps/dashboard/src/shared/lib/product/controller.hook.ts
import { useQuery, useMutation } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { appQueries } from "@/shared/api/queries";
import { appMutations } from "@/shared/api/mutations";
import { useActiveStoreStore } from "@/shared/lib/store/active.store";
import { useProductStore } from "./store";

export function useProductsController() {
  const { selectedStoreId } = useActiveStoreStore();
  const { page, limit, search, setSearch, setPage } = useProductStore();

  const query = useQuery(
    appQueries.product.all({ input: { storeId: selectedStoreId, page, limit, search } })
  );

  const deleteMutation = useMutation(appMutations.product.delete());

  return { ...query, page, search, setSearch, setPage, deleteMutation };
}
```

For isolated create/update forms, import `appMutations` directly without a controller hook.

### `shared/config/` — Configuration

```typescript
// Type-safe routing
import { RoutePaths } from "@/shared/config/routes";
<Link href={RoutePaths.PRODUCTS.INDEX.url}>Products</Link>

// i18n helpers
